
[1]futility

   FUTIL'ITY, n. Talkativeness; loquaciousness; loquacity. [In this sense,
   not now used.]

   1. Triflingness; unimportance; want of weight or effect; as, to expose
   the futility of arguments.

   2. The quality of producing no valuable effect, or of coming to
   nothing; as the futility of measures or schemes.
